article.headline: Marist 51, Iona 50
article.story: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. -- Dejuan Goodwin hit a game-winning jump shot from the top of the key with one second left to give Marist a 51-50 win over Iona on Friday. The Red Foxes jumped out to a 13-2 lead to start the game. They fended off the Gaels until midway through the second half, when Rashon Dwight gave Iona a 34-33 edge. The game went back-and-forth from there. Goodwin finished with 12 points and four rebounds for Marist (3-4, 1-0 MAAC). Ryan Schneider had 17 points and seven rebounds, and he made a leaning 3-pointer with 56 seconds left to put the Red Foxes within striking distance. Devon Clarke was the only player in double figures for Iona (2-4, 0-1 MAAC). He scored 11 points, going 5-for-5 from the free throw line. The Gaels missed all 10 of their 3-point attempts, while Marist shot 43 percent (9-for-21) from beyond the 3-point line.
